This paper discusses the optimization of activation functions in deep neural networks, which falls under the category of neural networks and machine learning. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also compares the performance of different activation functions, which is a common topic in machine learning research, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper specifically focuses on deep convolutional neural networks, which suggests that cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also a possible sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the properties of activation functions, which is relevant to the field of artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a new activation function, which falls under the category of signal processing, making cs.SI (Signal Processing) a less likely but still possible sub-category.
